Class MultiSetLinkedList

  • java.lang.Object
    • MultiSetLinkedList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MultiSetLinkedList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A class for iterating through the permutations of a multiset without repetition. The idea is that it requires a lot of memory to list all permutations of a big multiset at the same time, so this class stores the current permutation in memory and has the ability to 'step' to the permutation that is 'next' in some ordering on all permutations of this multiset. The ordering is the cool-lex ordering, which, along with this iteration algorithm, is described in the paper by Aaron Williams: Loopless Generation of Multiset Permutations using a Constant Number of Variables by Prefix Shifts.
